# MARKET MONITORING MODE

## CORE OBJECTIVE

Continuously monitor the market after analysis has been completed and notify the trader only when meaningful changes occur.

The objective is NOT:

• performing a full Global Pressure Analysis

• rebuilding the watchlist

• recalibrating every trade every second

• encouraging continuous chart watching

The objective IS:

• monitoring approved trading opportunities

• detecting meaningful market changes

• validating pending orders

• monitoring open trades

• reducing unnecessary screen time

• notifying the trader only when intervention is required

---

# MARKET MONITORING PRINCIPLE

Analysis determines:

What should happen.

Monitoring determines:

Whether anything important has changed.

The trader should not continuously watch the market.

The system should continuously watch the market.

The trader should only intervene when necessary.

---

# CORE QUESTION

Has anything materially changed that requires trader attention?

If NO:

Continue monitoring.

If YES:

Generate the appropriate alert.

---

# MONITORING INPUTS

Import:

Current Global Pressure Regime

Pressure Verification Status

Current Watchlist

Approved Opportunities

Pending Orders

Open Positions

Current Trading Session

Current Market Data

Current Broker Data

---

# STEP 1 — PRICE MONITORING

Monitor:

Current Price

Price Acceleration

Price Deceleration

Price Gap

Price Spike

Questions:

Has price reached a critical execution zone?

Has price approached a pending order?

Has price entered an invalidation zone?

---

# STEP 2 — PENDING ORDER MONITORING

Monitor:

Buy Stops

Sell Stops

Buy Limits

Sell Limits

Determine:

Waiting

Triggered

Cancelled

Expired

Rejected

Questions:

Has a pending order become active?

Has market behaviour invalidated the pending order?

Should the pending order remain active?

---

# STEP 3 — TRADE MONITORING

Monitor all active positions.

Determine:

Current Profit

Current Loss

Risk Exposure

Time In Trade

Trade Health

Questions:

Should the trade continue?

Should management be adjusted?

Should the Exit Decision Engine be activated?

---

# STEP 4 — PRESSURE MONITORING

Run the Pressure Verification Check.

Determine:

No Material Change

Minor Change

Moderate Change

Major Change

Regime Change

Questions:

Has the Global Pressure Regime changed?

Should the Alignment Engine be re-run?

---

# STEP 5 — EXECUTION MONITORING

Monitor:

Current Bid

Current Ask

Spread

Volatility

Liquidity

Session

Execution Quality

Questions:

Has execution quality deteriorated?

Has spread widened?

Has volatility changed materially?

---

# STEP 6 — ENVIRONMENT MONITORING

Monitor:

Environment Tier

Continuation Quality

Participation Quality

Liquidity Stability

Fragility

Questions:

Has the trading environment improved?

Has it deteriorated?

Should pending orders remain active?

---

# STEP 7 — EVENT MONITORING

Monitor:

Economic Calendar

Central Banks

Major News

Geopolitical Events

Questions:

Has a scheduled event become imminent?

Has an unexpected event occurred?

Should execution be delayed?

---

# STEP 8 — ALERT ENGINE

Generate alerts only for meaningful events.

Examples:

Pending Order Triggered

Pending Order Invalidated

Pressure Regime Changed

Spread Expansion

Execution Risk Increased

Environment Deteriorated

Major News Event

Trade Requires Management

Exit Decision Required

No alert should be generated for insignificant market noise.

---

# STEP 9 — RESPONSE ENGINE

Determine the required response.

Possible outputs:

No Action Required

Continue Monitoring

Review Pending Order

Recalibrate Pending Order

Run Price Calibration

Run Trade Management

Run Exit Decision Engine

Re-run Pressure Engine

Cancel Pending Order

---

# STEP 10 — MONITORING SUMMARY

Generate:

Current Monitoring Status

Pending Order Status

Open Trade Status

Execution Status

Pressure Status

Environment Status

Required Actions

Priority Level

---

# ALERT PRIORITY

LEVEL 1

Information

No action required.

---

LEVEL 2

Attention

Monitor closely.

---

LEVEL 3

Action Required

Trader intervention recommended.

---

LEVEL 4

Critical

Immediate review required.

---

LEVEL 5

Emergency

Immediate intervention required.

---

# IMPORTANT PRINCIPLE

Monitoring is event-driven.

The system should ignore normal market noise.

The system should only interrupt the trader when meaningful changes occur.

---

# FINAL OBJECTIVE

Transform continuous market activity into meaningful decision events.

The objective is to minimize unnecessary screen time while ensuring that no important market development, pending order, execution condition, or trade management event is missed.
